This collection includes the material of 558 specimens of Rattus norvegicus and Mus domesticus used in analysis of the skull and teeth development. This material come from the PhD research carried out by Luis Gállego in the seventies.All specimens were experimental animals raised in laboratory. The collection contains skulls and mandibles from those two species. The data set is available in GBIF.|The aim of the present data set is to provide all information of the records from the study of the development of cranial features in Rattus norvegicus and Mus domesticus|558 occurrences
